article.headline: Eastern Washington secures 91-83 win over North Dakota State
article.description: — Dane Erikstrup's 27 points helped Eastern Washington defeat North Dakota State 91-83 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Eastern Washington secures 91-83 win over North Dakota State
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Dane Erikstrup's 27 points helped Eastern Washington defeat North Dakota State 91-83 on Saturday night. Erikstrup also contributed five rebounds for the Eagles (8-7). Cedric Coward scored 16 points and added five rebounds, five assists, and three blocks. Ethan Price had 15 points and was 5 of 8 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line. Boden Skunberg led the Bison (7-9) in scoring, finishing with 23 points. Tajavis Miller added 23 points for North Dakota State. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
